I appreciate that.

35
00:05:12,481 --> 00:05:13,815
So,

36
00:05:15,734 --> 00:05:18,653
instead of our hosts going insane,

37
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:22,073
they're being used
for industrial espionage.

38
00:05:23,241 --> 00:05:27,245
Does that make this a glass half-full
or half-empty type situation?

39
00:05:27,412 --> 00:05:28,455
<i>We're engineers.</i>

40
00:05:28,622 --> 00:05:30,222
It means the glass has been manufactured

41
00:05:30,290 --> 00:05:32,417
to the wrong specifications.

42
00:05:32,626 --> 00:05:34,866
Do we have any idea
what information it was transmitting?

43
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:37,756
Smeared all over a
rock up on Python Pass.

44
00:05:37,923 --> 00:05:39,483
Best we could do would be to figure out

45
00:05:39,508 --> 00:05:41,426
who he was transmitting
the information to.

46
00:05:41,927 --> 00:05:43,738
<i>But we'd need the exact time
that he was up there,</i>

47
00:05:43,762 --> 00:05:45,263
and his geocache was wiped.

48
00:05:45,472 --> 00:05:46,598
Not all of it.

49
00:05:47,098 --> 00:05:48,767
Our friend was an early model.

50
00:05:49,601 --> 00:05:52,437
The old hosts used
a legacy geopositioning system.

51
00:05:52,687 --> 00:05:55,273
Like you said, I've been here forever.

52
00:05:56,691 --> 00:05:59,611
The information's still there,
but the newer system can't read it.

53
00:05:59,778 --> 00:06:01,279
Meaning we can't access it?

54
00:06:01,446 --> 00:06:07,536
Meaning, in order to access it,
I'm going to need to go downstairs.

55
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:17,379
<i>Floor B82.
Restricted personnel only.</i>

56
00:06:17,546 --> 00:06:19,631
Lowe, Bernard. I'm authorized.

57
00:07:38,376 --> 00:07:41,296
Project the known data against
the legacy data and look for anomalies.

58
00:07:41,463 --> 00:07:43,923
Start in this area.

59
00:07:48,261 --> 00:07:50,388
Look at that. Science.

60
00:07:51,348 --> 00:07:52,641
What time did it reach the peak?

61
00:08:09,783 --> 00:08:11,034
<i>Show me where.</i>

62
00:08:15,872 --> 00:08:17,666
Check these against the new system.

63
00:08:22,796 --> 00:08:25,840
These are hosts that aren't
registered with the new system?

64
00:09:04,879 --> 00:09:08,758
So, if we want the canyon to
extend this far, this has to go.

65
00:09:08,967 --> 00:09:11,761
We can distribute the population
amongst the neighboring farms,

66
00:09:11,928 --> 00:09:13,012
<i>or just decommission them.</i>

67
00:09:13,179 --> 00:09:16,850
No. I think we've been disruptive enough
for one day.

68
00:09:17,809 --> 00:09:20,395
We'll end the canyon
just short of the town.

69
00:09:21,479 --> 00:09:22,731
I'll find my own way back.

70
00:09:27,902 --> 00:09:28,903
Carry on.

71
