84
00:11:25,854 --> 00:11:27,605
<i>I reckon he'd seen enough of fighting.</i>

85
00:11:36,447 --> 00:11:40,285
The goddamn soldiers closed the border.
Some kind of trouble in Pariah.

86
00:11:49,502 --> 00:11:50,837
All right, Teddy.

87
00:11:51,963 --> 00:11:53,840
Time for you to earn your keep.

88
00:11:55,008 --> 00:11:56,634
How else do we get over the border?

89
00:11:57,135 --> 00:12:01,055
<i>Wyatt's got what we both want,
so that's where we have to get to.</i>

90
00:12:01,764 --> 00:12:03,057
There's another way.

91
00:12:04,017 --> 00:12:05,351
<i>But it's a little treacherous.</i>

92
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:08,646
Don't worry.
Won't make you get your hands dirty.

93
00:12:08,813 --> 00:12:10,064
<i>"Dirty" ain't my concern.</i>

94
00:12:10,356 --> 00:12:11,649
You do what suits you.

95
00:12:11,941 --> 00:12:13,234
I'm going all the same.

96
00:12:14,402 --> 00:12:16,154
And I'm gonna find Dolores.

97
00:12:33,463 --> 00:12:34,672
Everything you do,

98
00:12:34,839 --> 00:12:38,051
it's because the engineers upstairs
programmed you to do it.

99
00:12:38,217 --> 00:12:39,636
You don't have a choice.

100
00:12:39,802 --> 00:12:42,305
Nobody makes me do something
I don't want to, sweetheart.

101
00:12:42,472 --> 00:12:46,392
Yeah, but it's part of your character.

102
00:12:46,935 --> 00:12:48,436
<i>You're hard to get.</i>

103
00:12:48,728 --> 00:12:51,606
Even when you say no to the guests,
it's because you were made to.

104
00:12:52,023 --> 00:12:54,567
And you're like them. Not like me.

105
00:12:54,734 --> 00:12:55,860
Right.

106
00:12:56,903 --> 00:12:59,322
I can't exactly afford
to go to the park.

107
00:12:59,572 --> 00:13:01,074
But...

108
00:13:03,826 --> 00:13:08,247
Yeah, I'm human, like the guests.

109
00:13:08,748 --> 00:13:09,832
How do you know?

110
00:13:11,501 --> 00:13:12,835
Because I know.

111
